II. For the Accommodation of those who don't chuse to take the whole Work together, five Sheets will be deliver'd every Week, at the Price of Six-pence, to such of the Subscribers who are desirous of having it after that manner: By which Means the whole, when compleated, will cost but 1 l. 4 s. in Quires, and be finish'd in less than a 12 Month. The Proprietors are,
Samuel Ballard in Little Britain;
Benjamin Motte at the
Middle Temple Gate;
Richard Williamson near
Gray's-Inn-Gate, Holborn;
Samuel Birt in
Ave-Mary-Lane;
John Stagg in
Westminster-Hall;
Thomas Osborne in
Gray's-Inn; and
Charles Davis in
Pater-Noster-Row: By whom the Numbers will be delivered, as also by
James Roberts in
Warwick-Lane. Proposals at large, with a Specimen of the Work, to be had gratis at the above Places.
